Fairfax Media Says Computer Failure Disrupted Printing of N.Z. Newspapers

-- B y   T r a c y   W i t h e r s
-- 
2011-08-01T20:19:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/fairfax-media-says-computer-failure-disrupted-printing-of-n-z-newspapers.html
Fairfax Media Ltd. (FXJ)  was unable to
print many of its morning newspapers in  New Zealand  today after
a computer failure in its main production system.  Production of The Press in Christchurch, the Dominion Post
in Wellington, the Southland Times and the Timaru Herald were
affected, the company said in a statement on the stuff.co.nz
website, which it also produces.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tracy Withers at 
 twithers@bloomberg.net  